<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Add New Book</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>

<body>
    <!-- 
        ========================================================================
        CREATE BOOK FORM - EJS TEMPLATE
        ========================================================================
        
        CONCEPTS:
        1. HTML Forms: Used to collect user input
        2. Form Action: Specifies where to send form data (URL endpoint)
        3. Form Method: HTTP method to use (POST for creating data)
        4. Input Fields: Text inputs for collecting BookID, Title, Author
        5. Form Submission: When user clicks submit, browser sends POST request
        
        ========================================================================
    -->
    
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="heading">Add New Book</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- 
        HTML Form Element:
        - action="/add-book": The URL where form data will be sent
        - method="POST": Uses HTTP POST method (for creating new resources)
        - When form is submitted, browser sends POST request to /add-book
    -->
    <form action="/add-book" method="POST">
        <!-- 
            Input Field 1: Book ID
            - type="text": Text input field
            - name="BookID": Field name that will be sent in req.body.BookID
            - placeholder: Hint text shown when field is empty
            - required: HTML5 validation - field must be filled before submission
        -->
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="BookID">Book ID:</label>
            <input 
                type="text" 
                id="BookID" 
                name="BookID" 
                placeholder="Enter Book ID (e.g., 4)" 
                required
            >
        </div>

        <!-- 
            Input Field 2: Book Title
            - name="Title": Will be available as req.body.Title in server
        -->
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="Title">Title:</label>
            <input 
                type="text" 
                id="Title" 
                name="Title" 
                placeholder="Enter Book Title" 
                required
            >
        </div>

        <!-- 
            Input Field 3: Author Name
            - name="Author": Will be available as req.body.Author in server
        -->
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="Author">Author:</label>
            <input 
                type="text" 
                id="Author" 
                name="Author" 
                placeholder="Enter Author Name" 
                required
            >
        </div>

        <!-- 
            Submit Button:
            - type="submit": Triggers form submission when clicked
            - When clicked, browser collects all form data and sends POST request
        -->
        <button type="submit">Add Book</button>
        
        <!-- 
            Cancel/Back Link:
            - href="/": Link back to home page
            - Allows user to cancel and return to book list
        -->
        <a href="/">
            <button type="button">Cancel</button>
        </a>
    </form>

    <!-- 
        HOW FORM SUBMISSION WORKS:
        1. User fills in BookID, Title, and Author fields
        2. User clicks "Add Book" button
        3. Browser collects form data: { BookID: "...", Title: "...", Author: "..." }
        4. Browser sends HTTP POST request to /add-book with form data in body
        5. Express server receives request
        6. body-parser middleware parses form data into req.body
        7. Server route handler (app.post('/add-book')) processes the data
        8. Server creates new book and redirects to home page
        9. Browser follows redirect and displays updated book list
    -->
</body>

</html>
